2. If not auth → /auth/login or /auth/sign-up
3. Sign up with email/password
4. /onboarding (5 steps)
5. → /dashboard
6. User must add accounts manually
7. User must add transactions manually
8. Value emerges (balance visible, goals tracked)

**Conversion pain points:**

| Stage | Problem | Impact | Fix |
|-------|---------|--------|-----|
| **Sign up** | Email/password only | Friction vs. social login | Add Google/Apple sign-in |
| **Onboarding** | 5 steps, feature-focused | Drop-off at step 3-4 | Shorten to 3 steps, benefit-focused |
| **First account** | Manual entry | Friction, no "wow moment" | Show sample account, make it one tap |
| **First transaction** | Multi-step form | High friction | Voice entry or quick-add with defaults |
| **First value** | Requires setup before payoff | Users quit before payoff | Pre-populate with smart defaults or demo data |
| **Sticky value** | No daily hook | App becomes forgotten | Add daily check-in mechanic (FinScore, streaks) |

